The White House Press Secretary, Jay Carney, held a press briefing on May 15, 2013. He discussed a variety of topics including a meeting between President Obama and Senator McCain to discuss immigration reform and budget negotiations, the upcoming national conference on mental health, and the recent CBO report on deficit reduction. Carney also addressed the IRS scandal, stating that President Obama believes the conduct described in the Inspector General's report is inappropriate and wrong. He emphasized the need for action to be taken to hold those responsible accountable and to ensure that this type of conduct does not happen again. Carney also mentioned the President's support for a media shield law and the need to find a balance between the freedom of the press and the protection of national security.